HEADWORD: Parfleche
<hw>Par*fleche"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. through
Canadian F. fr. Amer. Indian.]</ety> <def>A kind of rawhide consisting
of hide, esp. of the buffalo, which has been soaked in crude wood-ash
lye to remove the hairs, and then dried.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

